## What is a static variable?

A **static variable** is a variable that is shared by all instances of a class. It is created by adding the `static`(#e7e8ea) keyword before the variable when it is declared.

```
 public class Student {
  public static String school = "Neighborhood HS";
  . . .
}
```

Use a **static variable** for attributes that are common (not unique) for all objects. For example:
- The name of the school for all students
- The name of the playlist for all songs 
- The number of apps on a cell phone 
- The number of employees at a business 

To use a **static variable**, use the `ClassName`(#e7e8ea) and the dot operator.
```
 public class StudentRunner {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println(Student.school);
  }
}
```
